President Biden is looking forward to welcoming President Guillermo Lasso of Ecuador to the White House on December 19, 2022. Special Presidential Advisor Chris Dodd met with President Lasso to deliver President Biden's invitation. The visit will allow the Presidents to discuss various regional and global issues, such as Russia's war in Ukraine. They will also emphasize the importance of strengthening democratic institutions and talk about regional economic integration initiatives, including the Americas Partnership for Economic Prosperity. Additionally, they will discuss economic and security cooperation, as well as Ecuador's leadership on regional migration.